<div id="review_413946722" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/413946722" />
    <a title="Shirley Frances" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4983961-shirley-frances"><img alt="Shirley Frances" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1610149034p2/4983961.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/413946722?book_show_action=true">Sep 13, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Shirley Frances" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Shirley Frances" href="/user/show/4983961-shirley-frances">Shirley Frances</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="ebook 9780985447137" href="/book/show/13974894-desire-by-blood">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4983961-shirley-frances?shelf=series">series</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4983961-shirley-frances?shelf=2012">2012</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4983961-shirley-frances?shelf=read-2-review">read-2-review</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4983961-shirley-frances?shelf=paranormal-fantasy">paranormal-fantasy</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer413946722" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14350556407966013462"><b>4.5 stars</b><br/><br/>I must admit that what first attracted me to this book was the cover. Come on, it&apos;s very HOT! Yes, I am one of those reader who likes to look at covers first and blurbs later. Luckily for me, this book had both!<br/><br/>This is my first read by Melissa Schroeder and my first Victorian Paranormal book, so I did not know what to expect. But the synopsis really captured my attention and I wanted to learn more. And boy am I glad I did!<br/><br/>The beginning of the book was a bit confusing since the author de</span>
  <span id="freeText14350556407966013462" style="display:none"><b>4.5 stars</b><br /><br />I must admit that what first attracted me to this book was the cover. Come on, it's very HOT! Yes, I am one of those reader who likes to look at covers first and blurbs later. Luckily for me, this book had both!<br /><br />This is my first read by Melissa Schroeder and my first Victorian Paranormal book, so I did not know what to expect. But the synopsis really captured my attention and I wanted to learn more. And boy am I glad I did!<br /><br />The beginning of the book was a bit confusing since the author delved right into the world she had created and I felt a little lost. But little by little I became fascinated by this new world of vampires - the 'Born' and the 'Made- and the Victorian society of the 'ton'.<br /><br />Lady Cordelia is an independent, strong woman who has had to make her own way in order to survive. Her assignment is to find out more about Nicodemus Blackburn, a Born vampire who is not looking to get attached. In an interesting and very hot turn of events, Cordelia finds herself compromised and married to Nico. Here their story begins.<br /><br />The author manages to give us glimpses of the their personalities early on, but once they are married they revealed a lot more about themselves. And their chemistry? Off the charts. The author managed to convey their every emotion - lust, frustration, anger, love - in a way that it flowed beautifully on the page and added that special something that made you feel for them and understand where each character was coming from. The secondary characters were an added bonus. Each one contributed to Nico and Cordelia's story in their own right. I especially liked Nico's mother Adelaide. Another great example of a strong woman in a time when they usually just followed a man's lead.<br /><br />The writing was excellent. I had no trouble, except at the very beginning, following the story and the world the author created. The series of events and the main plot were delivered at the right time which kept me intrigued and wanting more. I think that is why, when the resolution to the plot came to be, it felt a bit rushed to me. However, as a whole the book was great - strong and lovable characters, real emotions, interesting plot and hot chemistry. What more could you ask for? <br /><br />I look forward to reading the next book in the series. The excerpt of Malik's story was very interesting! </span>
  <a data-text-id="14350556407966013462" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


