<div id="review_424702274" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/424702274" />
    <a title="Lori" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/11479949-lori"><img alt="Lori" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1442006919p2/11479949.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/424702274?book_show_action=true">Sep 29, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Lori" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Lori" href="/user/show/11479949-lori">Lori</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/11479949-lori?shelf=erotic-romance">erotic-romance</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/11479949-lori?shelf=paranormal">paranormal</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/11479949-lori?shelf=vampires">vampires</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer424702274" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11826030574303919174">This author is very adept at her craft. She built strong characters, who oozed sexual chemistry, but also maintained a sense of humor. I loved the quick wit of the heroine Cordelia, in fact I almost wish the author had delved more into her personality. She will be an excellent supporting character in books to come, much like Adelaide will be. They are vibrant strong minded women, who turn to mush with their men. Nico is the alpha male we all crave, and his desire to protect his mate was sinfully</span>
  <span id="freeText11826030574303919174" style="display:none">This author is very adept at her craft. She built strong characters, who oozed sexual chemistry, but also maintained a sense of humor. I loved the quick wit of the heroine Cordelia, in fact I almost wish the author had delved more into her personality. She will be an excellent supporting character in books to come, much like Adelaide will be. They are vibrant strong minded women, who turn to mush with their men. Nico is the alpha male we all crave, and his desire to protect his mate was sinfully attractive.<br />If I had on critique it would be that I found the first couple of chapters difficult to enjoy, because the author jumped into this fantasy world very quickly. It threw me off kilter because there are so many aspects to this world that are unique, and must be learned. I think that a more thorough explanation earlier in the story about what a Made/Born was might have helped. Once I got past that, I was truly invested in the story. I can't wait to read about Malik and Diana, and I desperately want to see what type of woman could hold Saint's attention.<br />Overall a really good read, and I will be coming back for more.</span>
  <a data-text-id="11826030574303919174" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


