        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/406761881?book_show_action=true">Sep 03, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Daune Mc" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Daune Mc" href="/user/show/2194689-daune-mc">Daune Mc</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="ebook 9780985447137" href="/book/show/13974894-desire-by-blood">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer406761881" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8871841953884707740">: Desire by Blood (Kindle Edition)<br/>I was drawn into the story of Nicodemus Blackburn and Lady Cordelia Collingsworth.The reader is taken back in time to the Victorian era you feel as if you are there in London.At the balls and the warm lemonade it&apos;s these little things that help capture the feeling of the time. Melissa Schroeder gets you involved in her stories you feel like you are there with them. In this story the intrigue was so complying I could not put it down I keep reading and wondering w</span>
  <span id="freeText8871841953884707740" style="display:none">: Desire by Blood (Kindle Edition)<br />I was drawn into the story of Nicodemus Blackburn and Lady Cordelia Collingsworth.The reader is taken back in time to the Victorian era you feel as if you are there in London.At the balls and the warm lemonade it's these little things that help capture the feeling of the time. Melissa Schroeder gets you involved in her stories you feel like you are there with them. In this story the intrigue was so complying I could not put it down I keep reading and wondering what is going to happen next.Then there is the Melissa Schroeder passion that we have come to love. We see it happening between Nico a Born vampire and Cordelia a bluestocking trying to get an interview from Nico for a newspaper she writes for. Cordelia is trying to find out about Nico's finances how he makes his money.He doesn't know she is a reporter. When Nico and Cordelia see each other at the Smythe's ball we see the beginning of their passion.Melissa gives you a different look at vampires then you have read before at first it was a little confusing then you get it the more you read about them and their families.We meet Nico's parents,his cousin Saint and his best friend Malik a Made vampire.<br />I'm afraid if I say anymore I will give the whole story away.I look forward to the next story in this series. A must read!</span>
