<div id="review_2492884567" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2492884567" />
    <a title="Catlou" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/35145774-catlou"><img alt="Catlou" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1488394554p2/35145774.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2492884567?book_show_action=true">Aug 13, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Catlou" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Catlou" href="/user/show/35145774-catlou">Catlou</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/16052606-desire-by-blood">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2492884567" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5487223393776745921">Whether you are into the vampire paranormal romance genre or not, you will want to read this book! Vampires are generally not one of my favorites, but once I started this I could not put it down. You will adore Lady Cordelia. She’s a strong minded and strong-willed young woman who believes in speaking her mind. After being virtually abandoned by her family, she supports herself by making her way through the ton of London reporting on their activities and indiscretions for a local gossip newspape</span>
  <span id="freeText5487223393776745921" style="display:none">Whether you are into the vampire paranormal romance genre or not, you will want to read this book! Vampires are generally not one of my favorites, but once I started this I could not put it down. You will adore Lady Cordelia. She’s a strong minded and strong-willed young woman who believes in speaking her mind. After being virtually abandoned by her family, she supports herself by making her way through the ton of London reporting on their activities and indiscretions for a local gossip newspaper. Her current assignment is to find out what Nicodemus Blackburn is up to.<br /><br />You will fall in love with Nico Blackburn. He has a commanding presence &amp; is unaccountably drawn to Cordelia. Although not a member of the ton, he seems to carry a great deal of influence, which is what first sparked Cordelia’s interest as a reporter. Little does she know she’s about to get more than she bargained for but just what she needs.<br /><br />There’s a compromised reputation to save, secrets to reveal, made vamps to overcome, family history to uncover, a threat to their lives from the grave, and the ultimate question, to bond or not to bond. This story has drama, intrigue, suspense, a touch of humor, romance vampire style, and plenty of hot, steamy passion. Oh, I forgot to mention, you may shed a tear or two. This is a definite must read! I can’t wait to read Malik and Diana’s story next!!</span>
  <a data-text-id="5487223393776745921" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


