<span id="freeTextContainer13792927400717211095">I have to say for the most part, I have been torn between wanting to like this and not liking it. I started down with this story at a good 4.0 but about a 60% of the way there things started to really bug me. First came the set up for additional books. It was too obvious that the sister and Carrier victim would be books following this one. Then came to frequent attacks followed by the same intimacy scenes been basically the same motions of the very make out scene. The little things started addin</span>
  <span id="freeText13792927400717211095" style="display:none">I have to say for the most part, I have been torn between wanting to like this and not liking it. I started down with this story at a good 4.0 but about a 60% of the way there things started to really bug me. First came the set up for additional books. It was too obvious that the sister and Carrier victim would be books following this one. Then came to frequent attacks followed by the same intimacy scenes been basically the same motions of the very make out scene. The little things started adding up and by the end, I really do fell I can't give this story more than a three star.<br /><br />As for the things that did go right for the story was the fact that the lead chick didn't freak out like others tend to fall into. She was strong but I didn't feel her mother-in-law lived up to her reputation though. Editing was fine for the most part, but I did catch one towards the end. Spell checking wouldn't have caught it because the sentence on page 243 (eBook paged system); "They worked their way through the house ...” They would not have appeared incorrect. But that was the only I found.<br /><br />The author has the gift to write. I would only advise the skills to hone more towards content development.</span>
