<div id="review_2506326394" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2506326394" />
    <a title="JigsawGirl" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/24236699-jigsawgirl"><img alt="JigsawGirl" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1432166805p2/24236699.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2506326394?book_show_action=true">Aug 24, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="JigsawGirl" class="user" itemprop="url" name="JigsawGirl" href="/user/show/24236699-jigsawgirl">JigsawGirl</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2506326394" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1067774873106278339">I&apos;m not really sure how I felt about some of this book. I don&apos;t read vampire paranormal romances for the most part. I read this one because I enjoy Melissa Schroeder&apos;s work.<br/><br/>I was intrigued by the basic storyline. I liked Nico and Cordelia. I liked that Cordelia was outspoken and had a strong personality. The story started out well, but then it seemed to wander off the rails.<br/><br/>Between the Mades, the Borns, and the Carriers, it started to get a bit confusing. Then the mades could develop powers, but</span>
  <span id="freeText1067774873106278339" style="display:none">I'm not really sure how I felt about some of this book. I don't read vampire paranormal romances for the most part. I read this one because I enjoy Melissa Schroeder's work.<br /><br />I was intrigued by the basic storyline. I liked Nico and Cordelia. I liked that Cordelia was outspoken and had a strong personality. The story started out well, but then it seemed to wander off the rails.<br /><br />Between the Mades, the Borns, and the Carriers, it started to get a bit confusing. Then the mades could develop powers, but I was not sure if that occurred over time or as a result of being with a Born, or what.<br /><br />Then we have Nico, Malik, Gray, and Saint wandering around a little aimlessly looking for the vampire that was turning humans into Mades. I expected some big scene when they finally encountered that person, but, there wasn't one. Also, if Nico could make the person lose their cool that easily, then it should have been easier to flush the vampire out.<br /><br />I enjoyed most of the book with the exception of the vampire search and Nico not fully explaining Cordelia's situation to her. I liked most of the supporting characters.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1067774873106278339" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


